e of the written word over oral literature. Cornejo Polar decenters literature as the primary marker of Latin American cultural identity, emphasizing instead the interlacing of multiple narratives that generates the heterogeneity of contemporary Latin American culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Okt 2020) 0aBolivian literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aCulture in literature. 0aEcuadorian literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and societyxAndes Region. 0aPeruvian literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh1 aJentsch, Lynda J.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311071183740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822391913zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822391913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822391913.jpg  a978-3-11-071183-7  DUK Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles